This is gnome shell extension which draws energy beam like shape under windows.
This is clone of Nexus Live Wallpaper from android.

To install this extension, refer INSTALL.

Written by WSID ( http://wsidre.egloos.com, jongsome@naver.com )

################################################################################
1. Folder layout
################################################################################
Nexus-Extension/README			: This file.
Nexus-Extension/NEWS			: Update info of this extension.
Nexus-Extension/INSTALL			: Install instructions. PLEASE READ IT!
Nexus-Extension/nexus@wsidre.egloos.com	: Extension folder.
Nexus-Extension/schemas			: Folder which contains a gsettings 
					  schema which is used by this extension.
										  

################################################################################
2. Nexus-Extension/schemas
################################################################################
From version 0.3 the extension will use GSettings from GIO instead of using
extra values from metadata.json. Therefore, a proper schema file for gsettings
is needed.
Please refer INSTALL. If the schema file isn't installed properly, the extension
WILL BE CRUSHED and then, whole gnome shell.


################################################################################
3. PREALARM for DROPPING SUPPORT for gnome shell 3.0.x in next version
################################################################################
In 0.6, the next version, the extension will use functions from Clutter 1.8.
Therefore, it wouldn't be used with gnome shell 3.0.x which uses Clutter 1.0.
In other words, it will drop support for gnome shell 3.0.x in next version.

In this version, 0.5, the extension uses Clutter.CairoTexture.create() which is
in Clutter 1.0 but deprecated in 1.8.


################################################################################
5. Adjustment Parameters
################################################################################
There are some parameters to tune this extension. As this uses gsettings, we can
adjust parameters via gsetting editing tools. ( eg. dconf-editor, gsettigns... )

The schema the extension uses is "org.gnome.shell.extensions.nexus".

Parameter		= default	: description
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
pool-capacity		= 64	: Count of prebuilt and usable pellets. There
				  will not be pool extension. Therefore, no
				  spawning pellet when all of them are in use,
				  unless any of them gets out of screen and
				  recycled for next use.
				   Changes on this requires restart to take
				  effect.
				  
proceed-timeout		= 30	: Time interval of each step animation. Every
				  pellet moves in each stepping. It may be
				  considered as 'frame duration'.
				  
spawn-probability	= 0.3	: Spawning probability of each spawning timeout.
				  0 means no spawning, 1 means spawn pellet
				  every timeout.
				  
spawn-timeout		= 150	: Time interval of each spawning timeout. For
				  each spawning timeout, pellet spawning will
				  occur in probability of spawn-probability.
				  
speed-max		= 500	: Maximum speed of pellet.

speed-min		= 360	: Minimum speed of pellet.

pellet-colors		= ....	: The colors which pellets will use. Each pellet
				  will use one of the colors randomly. The
				  format of color should be understood by
				  gdk_rgba_parse(). ( For example,
				  rgba( 0, 0, 255, 1 ) or #0000FF or blue )
				  
pellet-default-alpha	= 0.3	: Default Alpha which is used for colors without
				  alpha value. For colors with their alpha
				  values, they will use their own. 0 means
				  transparent, 1 means opaque.
				  
pellet-trail-length	= 393	: Trail length of pellet.
				  
pellet-width		= 14	: Width of pellet.
				  
pellet-glow-radius	= 21	: Glowing radius of pellet.
				  
pellet-offset-x		= 0	: Offset of pellet plane. Leftmost pellet will
				  stick to left border of screen for offset (0,
				  0)
				  
pellet-offset-y		= 0	: Offset of pellet plane. Topmost pellet will
				  stick to top border of screen for offset (0,
				  0)

pellet-directions	= ....	: Directions of pellets. Each direction must be
				  one of 'UP', 'DOWN', 'LEFT', 'RIGHT'. Invalid
				  values will be ignored.
